# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Root .gitignore
# Rule of thumb:
#   .example / .template files  → COMMIT  (safe templates, no real secrets)
#   actual env / credential files → NEVER COMMIT
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Java compiled output ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.class
*.log
*.ctxt
.mtj.tmp/
*.jar
*.war
*.nar
*.ear
hs_err_pid*
replay_pid*

# ── Secrets and local overrides — NEVER COMMIT ────────────────────────────────
# The real .env with secrets (copy from .env.example and fill in values)
.env
# Any ad-hoc local yml overrides
*.local.yml
